      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_ContractLineUpdate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update a contract line in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.ContractLine",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. It also updates the corresponding contract totals in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.Contract",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table and logs the operation in an application log. Additionally, it records historical changes by calling another stored procedure, "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_HistoricalContractLineInsert",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The procedure handles exceptions by rolling back transactions and logging error details."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple operations, including updates to two tables, transaction management, error handling, and logging. The complexity arises from the need to maintain data integrity across related tables and ensure proper logging and error handling."
        }
      ]
    },
